message.content: cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CC. The paper deals with question answering and graph construction/traversal, which are common topics in natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves empirical evaluation and experimentation, which could fall under cs.LG (Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with the challenges of multi-hop inference, which could be relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
